  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">KKT-Empowering young men and women to advocate for peace and challenge hate speech in Myanmar.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A: 2.1.2: Support displaced women in Rakhine with a programme of digital literacy
(a) Sayama App 15 ToT will be trained
(b) 600 young IDP women will be trained by 15 ToT trainees 
Pilot the first Natural Language Processing Algorithm able to identify hate speech in Burmese:
A: 2.2.2: Establish a platform for monitoring real time hate speech in Myanmar: to engage youth led CSOs countering hate speech such as MIDO, Peaceful Myanmar Initiative, or the Panzagar movement, academics, policy experts, human rights NGOs and IT entrepreneurs.
A: 2.2.3: Bi-monthly meetings are organized between youth groups and OHCHR: to feed into the OHCHR Early Warning Mechanism specifically on the hate speech indicators.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IDP women will be more empowered on digital literacy, how to use mobile phone. They can then critically engage with
digital technology, rumors, staying safe online. First Natural Language Processing Algorithm will able to
identify hate speech in Burmese through virtual platform. OHCHR will also be benefited from the project as the findings of virtual platform around misinformation and disinformation will be fed into their early warning system in which they are tracking the possible conflict occurs.</narrative>
  </description>
